hrs earlier, and he was killed right after the patch. So, I'm thinking he is 3 days +/- some random amount.<P>Any pointers?  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Viscera Galen<BR>L60 High Priest of Brell<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Qamen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Any one have idea how long u need camp faction (from lowest to highest) and estimate how many goblin u need to kill ???<P>And then how many hp about those goblin (can a 60 cleric and 60 enchanter solo them ?)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kaysha Soulsinger</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">60 CLR and ENC don't solo, but duo :b<P>Anyway, yes, they can handle the Goblins easy. Each Goblin will give you +1 point of faction, you need roughly 3000 or so faction points to go from max KoS to max Ally. Luckily, you can also turn in Goblin Skins and Mineral Salts that both drop in the Gobbie areas to Herald Telcha (can be found at the Chardok zone). As long as your faction is anywhere reasonable (I believe Dubious is already enough), you will get +3 points of faction for each skin/salt you turn in.<P>------------------<BR>- Kaysha Soulsinger<BR>Templar in the 55th Circle of Erollisi Marr on Lanys T'Vyl<BR><I>The road to Heaven is paved with stones from Hell</I></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I decided to do the faction work at the exact same time that most of our Monks decided to.  Kind of caught me in suprise because I zoned into Droga, hit /who and was shocked to see 3 Affliction Monks chopping away.  Anyway, I joined them in the faction work.  I got my Second Ring and haven't bothered trying to get the third piece.  The Monks in my guild need it far more than I do and Drusella has been stingy to us (when we actually manage to find her up).<P>It took me about 3 weeks in between raids.  It actually took me the longest since I couldn't solo but the Monks LOVED having me there when I could.  There was zero downtime at all and we just pulled mini-trains of 4 or 5 goblins.<P>Depending how much time you devote to Droga, it really can go a lot faster but the key is finding a melee to partner with.  Soloing is possible but not efficient at all since there is a LOT of downtime.  It took me about 3 weeks but that was in between raids and other stuff.  When I actually could get there though, I was able to put in some time.<P>If you are soloing while waiting for a melee to pop into the zone.  I'd suggest doing the Warder area.  No real difference than other areas but just don't kill the Goblin Traitor (he's on Sarnak faction) and you have a chance to get a Shroud of Nature that sells for quite a bit (I gave a total of 5 to guild twinks and still sold 1 for myself).<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6975" TARGET=_blank>Quistil Angelwatch</A><BR>High Priest in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<P>Islington Angelwatch <BR>Cavalier of 53 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Forgot to add:<P>Higar,<P>HS is NORMALLY one of the most unused zones for high levels.  However, because of this quest, Drusella is killed on a regular basis.  She used to enjoy months of life but now her lifespan can be measured in hours.  Nearly all of the Monks in my guild want the Spirit Racked Cords so we try killing Dru whenever we can.  She doesn't always drop the Urn and we are competing with other people for it.  One guild in particular on my server has been keeping a good and solid lock on the quests bottlenecks (The gob in WW, Skargus, and Dru) while they equip their people in Chardok quest stuff.  I would bet that the same thing is happening on your server too.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6975" TARGET=_blank>Quistil Angelwatch</A><BR>High Priest in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<P>Islington Angelwatch <BR>Cavalier of 53 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShelseaDruid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Okies - when I started killing was KoS to Chardok.  How many goblins in Droga, Salts and etc do I need to kill to get enough to do ring 2?<P><P>------------------<BR>Hugs,<BR>Torriana Shaddowfists<BR>Loving Wife of Curius Shaddowfists<BR>60th Cleric<BR>Brell Serillis Server<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109127" TARGET=_blank>Profile</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Islington</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you receive Ring 1 by telling the Herald "I server the Sarnak" you have all of the faction you need to get Ring 2.  Takes about 3000 Gobling kills to get from max KOS to the faction needed for the Ring.  Skins/Salts are supposed to give between 1 and 3 points of faction (I've heard both).<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6975" TARGET=_blank>Quistil Angelwatch</A><BR>High Priest in the service to the Great Mother Tunare<P>Islington Angelwatch <BR>Cavalier of 53 Seasons in the glorious service to Erollisi Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thulseh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <A HREF="http://how.to/chardok" TARGET=_blank>http://how.to/chardok</A> <P> <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
